(e) during the first month following the end of each marketing year, of the quantities for which the deposits provided for in Article 5 (2) and Article 9 (2) of Regulation No 2114/71/EEC were forfeited during that marketing year.
2. However, if the quantities referred to in paragraph 1 (d) and (e) substantially exceed the quantities to be regarded as normal, the Member State concerned shall immediately inform the Commission.
3. If a Member State considers that the quantities for which applications for the advance fixing of the subsidy are lodged in accordance with the procedure in force bear no relation to the normal disposal of seeds harvested within the Community, that Member State shall immediately inform the Commission, indicating the quantities for which applications for the advance fixing of the subsidy have been lodged but for which the certificates have not yet been issued and the quantities for which advance fixing certificates have been issued since the last notification.

